description:
CapacityState: Table recording the capacity state of RAN cells at specific times.

dateTime: Timestamp of the capacity state record.
Area_Name: Name of the geographical area (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell.
Id2: Duplicate of CellId.
Id3:  Likely an internal identifier (always '1' in sample data).
Id4:  Appears to be a capacity key identifier.
vsDataType: Data type identifier (always 'vsDataCapacityState').
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format (always 'EricssonSpecificAttributes').
CapacityState.licensedCapacityLimitReached: Boolean indicating if licensed capacity limit is reached.
CapacityState.serviceState: Operational status of the cell (e.g., OPERABLE, INOPERABLE).
CapacityState.licenseState: License status of the cell (e.g., ENABLED, DISABLED).
CapacityState.grantedCapacityLevel: Level of granted capacity.
CapacityState.currentCapacityLimit: Current capacity limit (appears to be empty in sample data).
CapacityState.capacityStateId: Unique identifier for the capacity state.
CapacityState.description: Description of the capacity state.
CapacityState.keyId:  Unique key identifier for the capacity.
CapacityState.capacityKey: Detailed key identifying the capacity within the network.
